This cosmic duo helped scientists to understand pulsars better.

Pulsars are the mysterious remnants of certain stars that evolve and behave in ways that aren’t totally understood. But this pulsar system, J1023, acted as the perfect test subject: https://go.nasa.gov/4kGVBhG

To celebrate three years of studying the universe, 
@NASAWebb
 has clawed back the thick, dusty layers of the Cat's Paw Nebula. 

With its infrared vision, Webb can peer through clouds of gas and dust to uncover what lies beneath: https://go.nasa.gov/467QoMt

Congrats to Axiom Mission 4 on a successful splashdown! Missions like #Ax4 support research and outreach while developing the low Earth orbit economy, ultimately providing the government with reliable and safe access to space at a lower cost.

Ten years ago, New Horizons came closer to the surface of Pluto than any spacecraft in history, flying less than 8,000 miles (13,000 km) above the surface.

This enhanced-color image was taken when New Horizons was about 280,000 miles (450,000 km) away.

On July 17, at 11 a.m. EDT, we’ll hold a media briefing on our TRACERS mission and three additional NASA payloads launching on the same flight. TRACERS will study how Earth’s magnetic shield — the magnetosphere — protects our planet from the solar wind. https://go.nasa.gov/4653Z7e

NASA is deploying two aircraft to assist with state and local recovery efforts after destructive flooding near Kerrville, Texas. Airborne instruments are collecting high-resolution imagery and radar data to help map flooding, assess damage, and more.
